# Env schema sync

Changing `src/shared/config/env-schema.ts` or `.env.example`? Run **[env-schema-add](../skills/env-schema-add/SKILL.md)** — decide Secret vs Variable, place under the right `.env.example` half, run `pnpm tool:sync-env-example`, keep GitHub Environments in sync. `NODE_ENV` is `local | development | production` (default `local`; runtime never branches on it).

Non-negotiable env-flag principles (see the skill):

1. **Conditions live in the env layer** (`.refine()` in `env-schema.ts`); runtime code reads one specific `env.FLAG` and never re-derives the condition or combines flags.
2. **One thing → exactly one env variable** — never gate a single behaviour on two flags (`env.A && env.B`); collapse to one. (E.g. wipe helpers gate on `env.TEST_MODE` alone.)
3. **Casing** — env vars are `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`; a `snake_case` name like `debug_verification_code` is an API body field, not an env var.
